                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380618-name-136" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-136" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-136" type="surname" value="BEASELEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-136" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY BEASELEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am under ostler at the Coach-and-Horses, at Har<lb></lb>lington. On Sunday the 15th of April I pulled off my shirt, and laid it on my box—the prisoner was in the room—he was sleeping there—on the Monday morning, about five o'clock, I got up, and the head ostler with me—I left my shirt and the prisoner in the room—I did not come back till five o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner was then gone, and the shirt, and some other things—a man who sells shoes had been in the room—this is my shirt (<hi rend="italic">looking at one</hi>.)</p>
